Matrics are gearing up to rewrite the leaked Maths and Physics paper 2.There's been a backlash to the Basic Education department's decision from some teacher's unions. Masego talks to KwaZulu-Natal Education MEC, Kwazi Mshengu. #eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Kwazulu Natal Education Department wants to engage further with teacher unions about the rewrite of leaked matric exams. This, after the South African Democratic Teachers Union (SADTU) announced their plan to file court papers challenging the rewrite on Monday. Provincial MEC, Kwazi Mshengu, says he trusts  an agreement can be reached out of court. READ: Education dept were expecting resistance from unions The scheduled, first-ever, national rewrite by the Department of Education follows leaks of two papers. SADTU has labelled the decision by the department as irrational. Speaking to eNCA on Sunday, department spokesperson, Elijah Mhlanga, says they have been expecting legal resistance from unions. "It is a situation that we planned for. Our legal teams are considering all possibilities, in terms of what the response from the department is going to be," he said. For more, watch the interview above.